        {"question": "Do home sleep apnea tests work?", "answer": "Home tests are useful for many people with suspected obstructive sleep apnea, especially when symptoms are straightforward. They may miss UARS, complex sleep disorders, and some mild or positional cases, so persistent symptoms after a negative test should route to in-lab polysomnography."},
